Meet Your Author!

Click to edit text

Section colors
Duplicate section
Delete section

Hi My Name is Brandi King! I am a licensed Cosmetologist,Esthetician, and Barber. I started this blog to talk about healthy ways to keep you looking ravishing and replenished. Self care is the practice of taking care of yourself to promote your health and well-being. Self care is also something that most people forget to do or they don't know enough about. Blogs will be posted every week to update you.

Hooking my readers up with some hair and skin care do's, don'ts, and "why nots." During COVID, most people realized just how much effort it takes to maintain their hair and skin, gaining a newfound appreciation for their stylists. Now that things are back to normal, many are still opting to DIY to save a few bucks—but they often lack the know-how to do it right. I’m here to offer my readers easy, money-saving tips to help them achieve the gorgeous hair, glowing skin, and flawless nails they deserve.

"Consider making small changes to your own self-care costs to save big over time--you could switch to less expensive products and services or simply use them less often"(Natasha Etzel, June 2023) Saving money is all about stretching that mani-pedi to the limit and spacing out your hair dye sessions like a pro. Eventually, mastering a few at-home tricks means you can treat yourself *and* your wallet without sacrificing your glam! If you go from getting your nails done every 2 weeks to getting them done once a month, you are already cutting that expense in half. You can even take an online class for gel nails to start doing them at home. If you get your hair colored every 3 months instead of every 6-8 weeks you are saving on that as well.
